<br>
Ok /rant off, hehe I'm an old school fan. 5 would be my favorite, best storyline imo...however of the new gen 7 is my fav hands down.  Materia was simple but effective as a magic system, it started the epic FMV run for PS (I&quot;m talking hardcore CG, not cheesy movies).<br>
<br>
Mini Game? OMG I spend weeks in the Golden Saucer hehe. Chocobo races, Feed the Moomba..etc, Raising a Gold Chocobo, Ulimate weps...Content galore.<br>
<br>
In FF8...it was all game, game or nothing.  Like you said Barrin, you beat it in 30 hours...you could rush right through it and there was no penalty for that...to me thats not FF.  Drawing was a pain..Ultima and the other kick ass spells were in remote hidden locations where you basicaly NEEED a guide to find (although i was lucky enough to find the hidden island with out one)<br>
<br>
Poofing man said alot of things I agree with...over all I just didnt like the FF8 setting, it was too...Discotech.  I just didnt &quot;feel&quot; for the characters either...they seems bland and emotionless, well they were, lol.  I have no idea why but I was totaly involved with the Cloud/Tifa thing...I dont know if it was the setting, (Blade Runnerish/Future/Post Industrial) but I really felt part of the story...I guess although i play alot of Midevil games, im a sci fi nut at hear, and to me FF7 more accurately portrayed the future than FF8 did.<br>
<br>
The Card Game was fun at first...but it ended up just pising me off...half way though the game i have just about all the cards, even rares and I play to this guy...and he changes the rules on me...it go random..WTF and stupid me I acept the game, next thing I know I've lost my Cid and Half of my Summons.  So I I said screw it and turned the rest of the rare cards into items (which is probaly what ur suposed to do, i beat the game using 100 Heros I got from the Squall Card I believe)<br>
<br>
Ok...now the Trigger Gun and Zells combos were a good idea...but honestly, simplicity is one of the things I like about FF.  Storyline and character development is really what the serries is about...if i want hardcore RPG i play the Balders Gate Series or sumthing.  I wanted to use Zell, but got tired of doing combos, so I stuck to Squall, Questis (omg Blue magic owns), and Rinoa.<br>
<br>
I don't hate FF8 at all...its just my least fav.<br>
