<br>
So 6 (3 on SNES) and 7 didn't fit either?  They were both rather dark and gloomy for most of the game.  Since they weren't bright and cheery they didn't fit in with the FF line?<br>
I'm not opposed to the whole bright neon look, as long as it's in moderation.  8 didn't overdo it, IMO.  In 10 it was a bit much when the screens after battles (The ones that show you how much xp you got, items you won, etc.) look like a fooking scoreboard.<br>
Not saying I don't like 10.  I could just do without the excessive bright atmosphere.<br>
Also...experience and levels are a part of the FF series.  10 doesn't have those.<br>
Character themes were a part of the FF series.  9 didn't have those.  I can go on.  The only REAL thing that is a part of the final fantasy series is the name.  I hated 9.  I'm not yelling about how it shouldn't be in the FF series.  That's not up to me to decide.  That's is entirely up to the creators of the game.  I still have 9 on my shelf, because maybe someday I'll feel like playing it again.  Yes, I did play very far into it, forcing myself all the way, so it's not like I played 5 minutes of it and said it sucked.  If I remember correctly, I was near the end of the third disc.  Anyway...<br>
It's all just a matter of opinion.  But if you don't like the game, don't play it.  Ignore its place in the FF series if you have to.  Plain and simple. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaedhrosofnothing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maedhros of Nothing</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/051/45/30514540.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/30/02 6:42:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisfrm58.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=619.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why do so many ppl hate FF8?</span><hr size=1>   I liked FF 8, just not as much as the others. I liked the love theme, it was a nice change. The junction system was ok, not great not bad. The summoning was similar to 10, where you can have your monsters fight for you. But in 10 you can customize them alot more, teach them abilities, raise stats, plus you can win 99% of battles without summoning once. The pay by wage system was pretty cool too. The story line was somewhat absorbing...like how everyone would black out and then you'd have to play those 3 other guys(1st disc?), that sucked me right in. Otherwise, I think the draw system blew and I just couldn't quite get into the game. It felt like a chore to play it most of the time. I agree that everything in it looks pristine, almost to perfect. FFX was like this in a way but they sort of perfected it.<br>
